    <div class="moz-cite-prefix">Peter,<br>
      <br>
      So I think the problem with the wiki page is that it doesn't talk
      about the readme.txt file that's needed for Ushahidi to recognize
      the folder as containing a plugin. That does need to be changed.<br>
      <br>
      I've attached a hello world plugin. Drop the <i>helloworld</i>
      folder into the <i>/plugins</i> folder of your ushahidi install
      then activate it on the back-end. When you look at the main page
      you should see "Hello World" in big letters on the sites home
      page.<br>
      <br>
      I hope that helps.<br>
